<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,919,1825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Diagnosis. Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[516,720,919,944]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropenicillia">
<emphasis box="[516,720,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. nigropenicillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from their congeners by the gray­black patch of sex scales on each side of hindwing vein CuP. The male genitalia are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[488,643,999,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apenicillia">
<emphasis box="[488,643,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. apenicillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a somewhat undulate ventral edge of the valva, but the apex of the valva is less attenuate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,919,1825]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Description. Male forewing (
<figureCitation box="[664,753,1079,1105]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[312,1274,334,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[312,1274,326,1679]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Adult males of Ptychocroca. 28, P. apenicillia; 29, P. nigropenicillia; 30, P. keelioides, 31, P. lineabasalis; 32, P. crocoptycha; 33, P. crocoptycha; 34, P. galenia; 35, P. s i m p l e x." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168777/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[722,753,1079,1105]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="29.0">29</number>
</figureCitation>
) without patch of upraised scales near base of costa. Male hindwing with hairpencil concealed in fold of vein CuP, with patch of grayblack scales on each side of vein adjacent to haripencil. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1172,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="22.[264,382,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[319,1265,341,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[313,1273,329,1673]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Male genitalia of Ptychocroca; valvae spread, aedeagus removed (to left of capsule). 1, P. apenicillia; 2, P. nigropenicillia; 3, P. keelioides." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156575/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1156,1172,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with uncus, socii, and gnathos as described for the genus. Transtilla with large median lobe. Valva widest near middle, immediately beyond rounded excavation of venter, broadly triangular in distal 
<number box="[335,390,1279,1305]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.33">0.33</number>
; venter variably undulate; disc with weak trace of comb; large area of plication basally; angulation of sacculus weak. Aedeagus as described for genus; vesica with proximal group of cornuti not differentiated. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[957,1044,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="27.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[333,1273,327,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[313,1273,326,1670]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Female genitalia of Ptychocroca and Haemateulia. 16, P. apenicillia; 17, P. nigropenicillia; 18, P. keelioides; 19, P. lineabasalis; 20, P. galenia; 21, P. crocoptycha;" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156580/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1014,1044,1359,1385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
) with sterigma bearing slightly elongate lamella antevaginalis; anterior portion with a pair of triangular, membranous lobes; internal ventral sclerites in colliculum situated medially.
</paragraph>
